1. *Bitka* se vodila na otvorenom polju. (*Battle* was fought on an open field.)
2. Ratnici su *bitku* izgubili. (Warriors lost the *battle*.)
3. *Bitka* za nezavisnost bila je duga i teška. (The *struggle* for independence was long and hard.)
4. Vojska je *bitku* dobila zahvaljujući hrabrosti vojnika. (The army won the *battle* thanks to the courage of soldiers.)
5. Komandant je odveo svoje vojnike u *bitku*. (The commander led his soldiers into *battle*.)
6. Međunarodna *bitka* protiv klimatskih promena je neophodna. (The international *effort* against climate change is necessary.)
7. *Bitka* za pravdu se nastavlja iako su mnogi odustali. (The *fight* for justice continues even though many have given up.)
8. Nakon *bitke*, grad je bio uništen. (After the *battle*, the city was destroyed.)
9. Dva protivnika su se spremala za *bitku*. (Two opponents were preparing for a *duel*.)
10. Vojnici su se pripremali za *bitku* tako što su čitali strategijske knjige. (Soldiers were preparing for *battle* by reading strategic books.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "bitka" can have multiple meanings, such as "battle", "fight", "duel", "effort", "struggle", etc. Therefore, the translations provided may vary depending on the context.